HEADWORD: Flagitate
<hw>Flag"i*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>flagitatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>flagitare</ets> to demand. See
<er>Flagitious</er>.]</ety> <def>To importune; to demand fiercely or
with passion.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>
<rj><au>Carcyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

